I"ú<p>This is a cool tool, and automates some of which I had been doing manually - creating seeds for data. With one command, it will create a seed for a given table (or tables) using the data already within that table - beautiful. <a href="https://github.com/orangehill/iseed ">https://github.com/orangehill/iseed
</a></p>

<p style="text-align: center">
<div class="embed-container"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JtyaZTYNbl4" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>
</p>

<p>To install, add the package to your composer.json:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">"require": {
	"orangehill/iseed": "dev-master"
}</code></p>

<p>Run composer update:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">composer update</code></p>

<p>And the simplest command to generate a seed for a given table:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">php artisan iseed [table_name]</code></p>

<p>More commands / documentation are on the packages github page.</p>
:ET